✅ How to create a new file on GitHub (website)

Open your repository on github.com

At the top-right of the file list, click Add file

Choose Create new file

At the top, type your file name, for example:

README.md

notes.txt

script.sh

docker-learning.md

In the big text editor area, write whatever you want inside the file

Scroll down and find Commit changes

Optionally write a commit message (e.g., "Created notes file")

Click Commit new file
